The paper discusses the use of compressive sensing techniques in radar imaging systems, which involves signal processing and information theory (cs.IT), as well as statistical signal processing (cs.SP) and system and control theory (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a low complexity radar sensor design, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SP). Finally, the paper discusses recovery guarantees for structured measurement matrices, which could fall under statistical inference (cs.SI).
